HEADWORD: Levorotation
<hw>Le`vo*ro*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <altsp>[Written
also <asp>l⟦ae⟧vorotation</asp>.]</altsp> <ety>[<ets>Levo-</ets> +
<ets>rotation</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics & Chem.)</fld> <def>Rotation
in the direction of an outgoing right-handed screw; counter-clockwise
rotation; -- applied chiefly to the turning of the plane of polarization
of light.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

